SisterSplitTool is an image analysis platform developed to track sister chromatids. It is a post-processing tool for SegmentTrack_v4.0 software (https://github.com/ant-trullo/SegmentTrack_v4.0). This software is written in Pythonâ„¢ 3.10.12.

SisterSplitTool was developed and tested on the operating system Linux Ubuntu 24.04 64-bit.

Requirements: SisterSplitTool is written in Python3.10.12, but should work as well for newer versions of Python3. All the packages used by this software (with their version) are listed in the file requirements.txt: to install all of them should be sufficient to run the command 'pip install -r requirements.txt' in your console.

Install SisterSplitTool: Clone the repository and put all the files in a folder.

Run SisterSplitTool: Open a terminal (or cmd for Windows) move in the software folder and run 'python3 SistersSplitTool.py' and press enter. The graphical user interface will pop up and let you work.

Possible issues: Depending on the size of your data and the specifications of your computer, you can have a MemoryError. In this case try to shut down all the other tasks your pc is running and eventually crop your data.

For any question or issue send an email at: antonio.trullo@igmm.cnrs.fr